WEBVTT

00:06.136 --> 00:09.009
Welcome to the very end

00:09.139 --> 00:11.011
of the road not taken.

00:11.141 --> 00:13.535
Previously
onStar Trek: Picard...

00:13.665 --> 00:15.928
Q went back in time
and changed the present.

00:16.059 --> 00:17.887
-When was it?
-2024.

00:18.018 --> 00:20.150
In Los Angeles.
There is someone there to help.

00:20.281 --> 00:22.587
My name is Tallinn.
Pleasure to meet you.

00:22.718 --> 00:25.373
I have devoted my entire being

00:25.503 --> 00:27.288
to protecting one individual.

00:27.418 --> 00:28.811
Your ancestor.

00:30.117 --> 00:32.597
BORG QUEEN:
Agnes...

00:32.728 --> 00:34.556
-Let him go!
-I could take his body.

00:34.686 --> 00:37.037
-But it's you I want.
-[gunshot]

00:37.167 --> 00:39.126
-Agnes--
-No, i-it's not my blood.

00:39.256 --> 00:42.172
But I think I just killed
our only way home.

00:42.303 --> 00:44.218
WERNER:
Breaking the Shenzhen Convention

00:44.348 --> 00:46.002
has serious consequences.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.178
I'm doing this for our children.

00:48.309 --> 00:50.267
WERNER:
We have no choice
but to revoke your license

00:50.398 --> 00:52.487
-and your funding.
-Q: What a sad irony.

00:52.617 --> 00:54.532
A geneticist whose daughter

00:54.663 --> 00:56.839
has incurable genetic disease?

00:56.969 --> 00:59.320
Sunlight burns like fire?

00:59.450 --> 01:01.844
But you do have this.

01:01.974 --> 01:04.238
Analyze it.

01:04.368 --> 01:06.066
-[laughing]
-If you like what you see,

01:06.196 --> 01:08.372
give me a call. Then maybe...

01:08.503 --> 01:10.809
you can help me with something
that I might want.

01:10.940 --> 01:13.073
-[grunts, moaning]
-Kore?

01:13.203 --> 01:15.684
-No, no, no!
-[gasping]

01:15.814 --> 01:17.381
What do you need?

01:17.512 --> 01:20.123
Does the name "Picard"
mean anything to you?

01:20.254 --> 01:22.560
The Europa mission launches
in three days.

01:22.691 --> 01:24.997
I'm not sure Renée
will be on it.

01:25.128 --> 01:27.087
Are you ready for this?

01:27.217 --> 01:28.523
Are you gonna choke
when they need you?

01:28.653 --> 01:30.612
Because lives depend on it.

01:30.742 --> 01:32.092
And that scares me.

01:32.222 --> 01:33.571
SEVEN:
So no Europa mission,

01:33.702 --> 01:35.312
no Renée, no hope.

01:35.443 --> 01:36.661
Everyone hates everyone.

01:36.792 --> 01:39.447
We need to stop her
from quitting

01:39.577 --> 01:41.101
for the next 15 hours.

01:41.231 --> 01:42.580
She has to go
to the gala tonight.

01:42.711 --> 01:44.843
This is
a maximum security function.

01:44.974 --> 01:48.108
Each guest is issued
a radio frequency invite

01:48.238 --> 01:50.545
that corresponds
to a database of their entire

01:50.675 --> 01:52.112
life history.

01:52.242 --> 01:53.374
So we hack the database.

01:53.504 --> 01:55.724
Jurati will go in first,
infiltrate

01:55.854 --> 01:58.640
security and inject our IDs

01:58.770 --> 02:01.773
-into the system.
-It worked.

02:01.904 --> 02:03.645
-I'm inside
the surveillance room.
-Excellent.

02:03.775 --> 02:05.299
Waiting for your signal.

02:05.429 --> 02:07.736
BORG QUEEN:
Once I'm gone, you are alone.

02:07.866 --> 02:10.521
You need me, Agnes.

02:10.652 --> 02:12.436
Need me, Agnes.

02:15.309 --> 02:16.788
RIOS:
Admiral, can you hear me?

02:16.919 --> 02:18.138
TALLIN:
Jean-Luc?

02:18.268 --> 02:19.835
RIOS:
Don't go. Stay with us.

02:19.965 --> 02:22.098
Admiral, are you okay?

02:22.229 --> 02:23.752
TALLINN:
Jean-Luc?

02:23.882 --> 02:25.928
BOY:
Maman!

02:27.234 --> 02:29.366
-Admiral?
-Rios, is he okay?

02:29.497 --> 02:32.064
-Stay with us, Jean-Luc.
-WOMAN: Then come find me.

02:32.195 --> 02:33.718
TALLINN:
Okay, we have to get him
to a hospital.

02:33.849 --> 02:36.286
-[speaking French]
-What about your ship?

02:36.417 --> 02:38.158
Maman!

02:38.288 --> 02:39.507
[boy shouts]

02:40.769 --> 02:42.945
[lively jazz music playing]

02:43.075 --> 02:45.121
[indistinct chatter]

02:52.215 --> 02:53.912
You did it again.

02:54.043 --> 02:55.697
What?

02:55.827 --> 02:57.829
You called me Laris.

02:57.960 --> 02:59.788
I thought, uh,

02:59.918 --> 03:01.659
you might be an ancestor.

03:01.790 --> 03:03.835
But she's Romulan, so, um,

03:03.966 --> 03:05.707
didn't seem possible.

03:05.837 --> 03:08.275
You know,
your voice does this...

03:08.405 --> 03:10.712
funny little thing
when you say her name.

03:13.628 --> 03:15.282
Who is she, anyhow?

03:15.412 --> 03:17.849
Oh, no one of importance.

03:17.980 --> 03:19.895
Thanks for that.

03:20.025 --> 03:22.289
Now I know what it looks like
when you lie.

03:23.855 --> 03:26.075
PICARD:
Rios, let's take our positions.

03:26.206 --> 03:28.643
Once Jurati clones our IDs
onto these bracelets,

03:28.773 --> 03:30.645
we can get past security.

03:31.863 --> 03:34.214
TALLINN:
And then we won't have to
worry about facial recognition

03:34.344 --> 03:36.216
-once we're inside.
-Jurati?

03:36.346 --> 03:38.218
What's your status?

03:38.348 --> 03:39.828
BORG QUEEN:
Agnes...

03:39.958 --> 03:42.047
-PICARD: Jurati?
-[Borg Queen whispering]

03:42.178 --> 03:44.224
Jurati...

03:44.354 --> 03:46.182
JURATI:
I'm in position.

03:46.313 --> 03:48.837
PICARD:
Good. We're ready when you are.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.756
Captured on purpose.

03:54.886 --> 03:56.236
Clever little plan.

03:56.366 --> 03:57.976
I do miss Locutus.

03:58.107 --> 04:00.327
I'm 100% sure
he doesn't miss you.

04:00.457 --> 04:02.198
PICARD:
Picard to Jurati,

04:02.329 --> 04:03.895
the line is moving.

04:04.026 --> 04:06.463
I need you to speed things up.

04:06.594 --> 04:09.205
Copy that, uh, give me 60.

04:16.778 --> 04:18.649
The key's in his pocket.

04:18.780 --> 04:20.825
I know.

04:26.440 --> 04:27.876
You probably should have waited
until he was

04:28.006 --> 04:29.834
standing a bit closer to you.

04:29.965 --> 04:32.968
You don't look
like a 60-year-old southern

04:33.098 --> 04:35.536
-heart surgeon.
-There must be a mistake.

04:35.666 --> 04:37.189
[grunting]

04:37.320 --> 04:38.800
Here, try again.

04:38.930 --> 04:40.628
If you'd like to give me
a little more control,

04:40.758 --> 04:43.195
I could help you.

04:46.329 --> 04:48.331
PICARD:
Jurati, we're out of time!

04:48.462 --> 04:49.985
Fine, I give up!

04:50.115 --> 04:51.987
Help me.

04:52.117 --> 04:54.206
Pull.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.214
IDs uploading.

05:03.564 --> 05:05.696
SECURITY GUARD:
You're good.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.872
Enjoy your evening.

05:09.831 --> 05:12.181
PICARD:
Thank you.

05:12.312 --> 05:13.748
Better late than never.

05:13.878 --> 05:15.445
But I knew you could do it.

05:15.576 --> 05:17.317
-[exhales]
-You're welcome.

05:17.447 --> 05:18.883
[groans]
If you don't shut up,

05:19.014 --> 05:20.407
I will find a way
to destroy you.

05:20.537 --> 05:22.147
I beg your pardon?

05:22.278 --> 05:24.367
[stammers]
No, sorry, not for you.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.064
Let's go. They'll be waking soon

05:26.195 --> 05:28.110
with some short-term memory loss
and I'd like to get back

05:28.240 --> 05:30.721
to enjoying my-- our...

05:30.852 --> 05:33.289
evening.

05:42.603 --> 05:44.648
♪

06:13.851 --> 06:16.419
♪

06:46.101 --> 06:48.146
♪

07:18.786 --> 07:20.831
♪

07:39.981 --> 07:41.983
RIOS:
He's not gonna make it.

07:42.113 --> 07:43.288
-TALLINN: There must be
something...
-RIOS: We're losing him!

07:43.419 --> 07:44.812
TALLINN:
Stay with us, Jean-Luc.

07:44.942 --> 07:46.466
-Quick, do something!
-What's happening to him?

07:46.596 --> 07:48.642
RIOS: Quick, do something!
He's flatlining.

07:48.772 --> 07:50.774
[woman screams]

07:51.906 --> 07:53.908
WOMAN:
No!

07:56.040 --> 07:58.303
[lively jazz music playing]

08:18.062 --> 08:20.195
MUSA:
Picard!

08:21.152 --> 08:22.763
Picard?

08:22.893 --> 08:24.504
Get in here.

08:24.634 --> 08:27.028
That's an order.

08:28.203 --> 08:30.248
-[chuckles]
-[indistinct chatter]

08:31.380 --> 08:33.295
It's nice to meet you.

08:33.425 --> 08:35.993
I'd say so far so good.

08:36.124 --> 08:38.387
-But you know her best.
-Ah...

08:38.518 --> 08:40.824
she looks all right,
but she's gotten

08:40.955 --> 08:42.870
pretty good
at putting on an act.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.568
There's this thing

08:45.699 --> 08:47.483
she does with her earlobe.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.485
Truth is,

08:49.616 --> 08:51.531
I've been
protecting Renée from afar

08:51.661 --> 08:53.315
for 24 years.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.360
I may have lost my touch
a little when it comes

08:55.491 --> 08:57.841
to engaging with humans.

08:57.972 --> 09:00.714
You've never spoken to her

09:00.844 --> 09:02.803
in all those years?

09:02.933 --> 09:05.893
It's not just a rule,
it's a code we live by.

09:06.023 --> 09:07.895
No connection.

09:08.025 --> 09:10.114
I'm a ghost.

09:10.245 --> 09:13.074
It's the best way
to keep her safe.

09:15.032 --> 09:17.731
And who is watching over you?

09:25.303 --> 09:28.132
Ten hours to quarantine, Picard.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.787
We just need
to keep Renée safe till then.

09:39.622 --> 09:41.493
♪

09:41.624 --> 09:44.453
[indistinct chatter]

09:50.328 --> 09:52.200
Who are we tonight, Agnes?

09:52.330 --> 09:53.418
I like it.

09:53.549 --> 09:55.551
There is no "we."

09:55.682 --> 09:57.292
I believe that's the proper
pronoun for when one

09:57.422 --> 09:59.555
shares one's body
with one's new friend.

09:59.686 --> 10:01.992
We are not sharing.
You are a houseguest.

10:02.123 --> 10:03.994
It's just until I can figure out
what to do with you.

10:04.125 --> 10:06.344
BORG QUEEN:
You just couldn't let me die.

10:06.475 --> 10:08.346
You are not the one I'm saving.

10:08.477 --> 10:10.087
Now we're splitting hairs.

10:10.218 --> 10:12.916
Oh, it was fun
lying to your friends.

10:13.047 --> 10:15.527
Especially the one
you had intercourse with.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.138
It wasn't fun at all.

10:17.268 --> 10:18.879
Not the intercourse, that was...

10:19.009 --> 10:21.098
[stammers]
I hated lying to my friends.

10:21.229 --> 10:23.361
It was an impossible choice.

10:23.492 --> 10:25.059
Couldn't let the cop die,
but I couldn't kill

10:25.189 --> 10:26.713
the one thing
that could get us home, either.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.715
It's the best thing
for everyone.

10:28.845 --> 10:30.542
BORG QUEEN:
Keep telling yourself that,
dear.

10:30.673 --> 10:32.109
Will you stop talking?

10:32.240 --> 10:34.546
-Enough shop talk, let's play.
-No!

10:34.677 --> 10:36.287
There's no play-- no playing.

10:36.418 --> 10:38.638
I told you I have
a mission to accomplish.

10:38.768 --> 10:40.117
I'm just saying all of these

10:40.248 --> 10:41.858
stress hormones
aren't good for us.

10:41.989 --> 10:43.904
I don't mind
a little shot of adrenaline

10:44.034 --> 10:45.775
with a norepinephrine chaser,
but...

10:45.906 --> 10:48.430
I'd say we're past the optimal
amounts of cortisol here.

10:48.560 --> 10:50.562
But whatever you say, I guess.

10:50.693 --> 10:53.130
You're in control here.

10:55.176 --> 10:57.657
BARTENDER:
What can I get you?

10:59.746 --> 11:01.835
-Club soda, please?
-Certainly.

11:01.965 --> 11:03.663
RIOS:
Hey, Raf?

11:03.793 --> 11:05.839
Perimeter's clear.

11:05.969 --> 11:07.754
Looks like Renée's keeping busy.

11:07.884 --> 11:10.321
And there's no sign of Q.

11:10.452 --> 11:13.760
Oh, wait for it, wait for it.

11:13.890 --> 11:16.197
-[singsongy]: Ta-da!
-[laughs]

11:16.327 --> 11:18.025
It's real, Raffi.

11:18.155 --> 11:19.766
[inhales deeply]
Ay-ya-ya.

11:19.896 --> 11:22.029
-I mean, you've got to--
-No, I'm good, sweetie.

11:22.986 --> 11:25.336
Have you ever seen
actual matches like this?

11:25.467 --> 11:26.860
Where they come in bunches

11:26.990 --> 11:28.818
under this little cover.

11:28.949 --> 11:30.994
Who-who is this?
This whole thing here.

11:31.125 --> 11:32.430
This glow.

11:32.561 --> 11:33.997
It's like you're...

11:34.128 --> 11:35.390
happy.

11:35.520 --> 11:37.566
I'm just making
the best of things.

11:37.697 --> 11:40.003
Mm-hmm. well, I know you.

11:40.134 --> 11:43.137
So I find that alarming.

11:44.791 --> 11:46.706
21st-century Earth isn't
what I thought it would be.

11:46.836 --> 11:48.969
-Mm.
-Everything's so intense.

11:49.099 --> 11:51.319
All the cars
and the honking and shouting.

11:51.449 --> 11:52.886
It's dirty.

11:53.016 --> 11:55.149
Music everywhere.

11:55.279 --> 11:57.151
Ah.

11:57.281 --> 11:58.805
The food is amazing.

11:58.935 --> 12:00.632
-The cigars.
-Yeah.

12:00.763 --> 12:02.504
It's not just that.

12:02.634 --> 12:05.463
No, you've been walking around
with that big, goofy smile

12:05.594 --> 12:07.814
on your face
ever since you were locked up

12:07.944 --> 12:10.207
with that doctor.

12:12.209 --> 12:14.429
Did you know that she built
that clinic from the ground up?

12:14.559 --> 12:16.997
The people in that community
had nowhere to go

12:17.127 --> 12:18.912
until she got there.

12:19.042 --> 12:21.305
-She saves lives.
-Rios.

12:21.436 --> 12:23.568
Do not even think
about going there.

12:26.963 --> 12:28.617
[exhales]
I'm trying not to.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.314
Try harder.

12:30.445 --> 12:32.708
Because when you meet someone
from a different century,

12:32.839 --> 12:35.842
the relationship is
kind of built on lies.

12:37.800 --> 12:39.584
[nearby laughter]

12:39.715 --> 12:41.543
RIOS:
Someone's enjoying themselves.

12:41.673 --> 12:43.197
RAFFI:
Mm-hmm.

12:43.327 --> 12:46.113
There's a lot of baggage
with those Borg implants.

12:46.243 --> 12:49.246
It's kind of nice to see
her travel light for a while.

12:58.255 --> 12:59.691
[gasps]

13:04.000 --> 13:06.176
[exhales]

13:14.881 --> 13:17.448
Does she normally drink
like that?

13:17.579 --> 13:19.973
Well, she's going
into quarantine tomorrow.

13:20.103 --> 13:22.758
Maybe it's a last hurrah.

13:25.935 --> 13:28.329
She's doing the thing
with the ear.

13:28.459 --> 13:30.853
That usually means the beginning
of a downward spiral.

13:30.984 --> 13:33.334
I've got an intercept program.

13:33.464 --> 13:35.292
I'm gonna see who she's texting.

13:35.423 --> 13:36.903
She does seem to check

13:37.033 --> 13:38.818
her mobile device quite a bit.

13:38.948 --> 13:40.428
Oh, we all do that.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.127
[speaks Romulan]

13:44.258 --> 13:46.608
She's texting her therapist.

13:46.738 --> 13:49.480
Q, whatever.
"I can't do this.

13:49.611 --> 13:51.439
"I'm not ready for this mission.

13:51.569 --> 13:53.223
"When this party is over,

13:53.354 --> 13:55.269
I'm gonna tell Musa I'm out."

13:55.399 --> 13:57.837
And Q is encouraging her
to quit.

13:57.967 --> 13:59.795
Which is Musa?

13:59.926 --> 14:02.842
Uh, the mission commander.
Her boss.

14:02.972 --> 14:05.105
I am going to speak with Renée.

14:05.235 --> 14:07.455
Uh-uh,
we're not breaking the code.

14:07.585 --> 14:09.805
It's kept Renée safe
her entire life.

14:09.936 --> 14:12.199
-I understand that...
-What if Q is right?

14:12.329 --> 14:14.592
What if she's not ready?

14:14.723 --> 14:16.768
Perhaps...

14:16.899 --> 14:19.162
it's you who is not ready.

14:19.293 --> 14:22.252
This is her destiny.

14:22.383 --> 14:24.689
You've done a good job.

14:24.820 --> 14:27.083
Now let her go.

14:29.651 --> 14:31.653
All right.

14:32.915 --> 14:34.656
It will help our odds

14:34.786 --> 14:37.050
if we can get Commander Musa
out of play.

14:37.180 --> 14:40.053
Yeah. We need Dr. Jurati.
She speaks his language.

14:40.183 --> 14:42.533
Picard to Jurati.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.623
Picard to Jurati.

14:45.754 --> 14:47.887
BORG QUEEN:
Feeling better?

14:48.017 --> 14:49.889
We needed a little break.

14:50.019 --> 14:51.455
I just want you
to live a little,

14:51.586 --> 14:52.761
but there's only so much
I can do.

14:52.892 --> 14:53.762
That's by design.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.242
This is 50/50, remember?

14:55.372 --> 14:56.765
Champagne, please.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.376
-Of course.
-BORG QUEEN: I've noticed

14:59.507 --> 15:01.030
we've been getting
some attention this evening.

15:01.161 --> 15:02.510
It's the dress.

15:02.640 --> 15:04.686
It's us. Together.

15:06.209 --> 15:08.472
You're showing your potential.

15:09.778 --> 15:11.693
Is your communicator down?

15:11.823 --> 15:12.955
-Picard's calling you.
-Oh.

15:13.086 --> 15:14.870
I'm sorry. I-I think we, um,

15:15.001 --> 15:16.872
I must've accidentally
turned it off.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.569
Are you doing all right?

15:18.700 --> 15:20.963
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm..

15:21.094 --> 15:23.009
Do you want to sit down?
You can lean on me.

15:23.139 --> 15:25.054
I know.

15:25.185 --> 15:26.751
You were great that way.

15:26.882 --> 15:28.405
Agnes,
you've been through a lot.

15:28.536 --> 15:31.017
Just a few hours ago,
you had blood on your hands.

15:31.147 --> 15:33.193
Your eyebrows are doing
that cute little thing

15:33.323 --> 15:35.673
they do
when you're worried about me.

15:35.804 --> 15:38.633
I just want you to tell me
what's going on with you.

15:38.763 --> 15:40.940
-Why?
-Because...

15:41.070 --> 15:43.116
I care about you.

15:43.246 --> 15:45.379
You know that.

15:45.509 --> 15:47.337
BORG QUEEN:
Don't let fear get in the way.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.950
Allow me.

15:52.821 --> 15:54.954
Oh, that was a strong pull.

15:55.084 --> 15:56.216
Um...

15:56.346 --> 15:57.695
That's, that's not what I meant.

15:57.826 --> 15:59.784
No, I'm sorry. I think I'm--

15:59.915 --> 16:01.438
I'm just not myself tonight.

16:01.569 --> 16:03.614
No, it's, uh...

16:09.359 --> 16:10.708
MAN [over radio]:
Counter thrusters are off-line.

16:10.839 --> 16:12.101
Brace position.

16:12.232 --> 16:14.364
-[alarm blaring]
-Cutoff unresponsive.

16:14.495 --> 16:16.192
Impact. Three...

16:16.323 --> 16:17.672
two...

16:17.802 --> 16:19.979
one.

16:25.593 --> 16:27.595
Okay.
[shudders]

16:27.725 --> 16:29.597
All right.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.776
TALLINN:
Where's she going?

16:34.906 --> 16:36.691
PICARD:
I don't know,
but we can't wait for Jurati.

16:36.821 --> 16:38.519
TALLINN:
It's now or never.

16:39.520 --> 16:41.130
What are you gonna say
to convince her?

16:42.392 --> 16:44.438
I'm not quite sure.

16:46.396 --> 16:48.442
Picard.

16:54.752 --> 16:56.841
Adam Soong.

17:00.497 --> 17:02.630
I believe we have
a friend in common.

17:03.631 --> 17:05.633
A Mr. Q.

17:08.418 --> 17:10.203
He's not a friend.

17:10.333 --> 17:12.379
-That's what he said about you.
-Listen to me.

17:12.509 --> 17:14.772
Have nothing to do with him.

17:14.903 --> 17:16.731
I have no interest

17:16.861 --> 17:18.646
in being part of some...

17:18.776 --> 17:20.691
whatever this is...

17:20.822 --> 17:22.432
so do yourself a favor.

17:22.563 --> 17:24.043
Walk away.

17:24.173 --> 17:26.610
I can't allow Renée
to complete this mission.

17:26.741 --> 17:28.786
Stay away from her.

17:28.917 --> 17:31.093
I could say the same to you.

17:31.224 --> 17:32.834
I don't have a choice.

17:32.964 --> 17:35.054
You really don't understand

17:35.184 --> 17:37.708
who you're dealing with.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.233
Neither do you.

17:40.363 --> 17:41.799
Dr. Soong.

17:41.930 --> 17:44.063
Thank you
for the generous donation

17:44.193 --> 17:45.542
to the Europa Mission.

17:45.673 --> 17:47.631
I'm in shock.
Welcome to the board.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.111
Hmm.

17:49.242 --> 17:51.548
Anything we can do for you?
A VIP tour?

17:51.679 --> 17:53.811
Actually, there is something.

17:53.942 --> 17:57.076
[whispering]:
That gentleman is dangerous.

18:15.920 --> 18:17.052
-TALLINN: Stay with us,
Jean-Luc.
-RIOS: Don't go.

18:17.183 --> 18:19.272
Don't leave us!
We're losing him!

18:19.402 --> 18:21.100
TERESA:
Clear!

18:22.492 --> 18:24.538
WOMAN:
Jean-Luc. Look up.

18:27.758 --> 18:30.718
♪

18:32.850 --> 18:35.592
Guys, I think
I'm in trouble here.

18:35.723 --> 18:38.247
[indistinct chatter]

18:45.211 --> 18:47.126
I've lost Renée.

18:47.256 --> 18:49.215
-Does anyone have her?
-RIOS: I do.

18:49.345 --> 18:51.130
She's on the move.

18:54.089 --> 18:56.004
You can't push me like that.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.701
BORG QUEEN:
I'm trying to get you
to understand

18:57.832 --> 18:59.747
that good things happen
when you lose control.

18:59.877 --> 19:02.750
Tallinn, I could use some help
down here.

19:06.971 --> 19:08.321
RIOS:
Admiral, I don't know
how much longer

19:08.451 --> 19:09.931
Renée's gonna stick around.

19:10.061 --> 19:11.889
We're jeopardizing the mission.
We need to leave.

19:12.020 --> 19:13.587
BORG QUEEN:
Don't be ridiculous.

19:13.717 --> 19:15.806
RAFFI:
Jean-Luc?

19:15.937 --> 19:18.113
They've got the exits covered.

19:18.244 --> 19:20.159
PICARD:
Tallinn, they've got us
surrounded.

19:20.289 --> 19:23.031
BORG QUEEN:
You want to help? Let's help.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.686
Your friends need a distraction.

19:27.166 --> 19:29.559
Initiating
nano-electronic pulse.

19:29.690 --> 19:31.866
Lights out, Agnes.

19:31.996 --> 19:34.347
Now get to work.

19:34.477 --> 19:36.914
[crowd groaning, murmuring]

19:39.526 --> 19:41.441
Quick, now we can go.

19:41.571 --> 19:44.139
JURATI:
♪ We're running
with the shadows♪

19:44.270 --> 19:46.794
♪ Of the night♪

19:46.924 --> 19:51.799
♪ Baby take my hand,
you'll be all right♪

19:53.061 --> 19:55.542
♪ Surrender all your dreams♪

19:55.672 --> 19:58.980
♪ To me tonight♪

20:00.068 --> 20:01.635
♪ They'll come true♪

20:01.765 --> 20:03.811
♪ In the end♪

20:03.941 --> 20:05.987
[band playing
accompanying music]

20:12.080 --> 20:14.082
♪ Oh, girl♪

20:14.213 --> 20:16.345
♪ It's a cold world♪

20:16.476 --> 20:19.392
♪ When you keep it all
to yourself♪

20:21.045 --> 20:25.354
♪ Now you can't hide
on the inside♪

20:25.485 --> 20:28.792
♪ All the pain
you've ever felt♪

20:31.099 --> 20:34.624
♪ Ransom my heart,
but, baby, don't look back♪

20:34.755 --> 20:38.846
♪ 'Cause we got nobody else♪

20:40.543 --> 20:45.156
♪ We're running
with the shadows of the night ♪

20:45.287 --> 20:49.639
♪ Baby, take my hand,
you'll be all right♪

20:49.770 --> 20:52.555
♪ Surrender
all your dreams to me♪

20:52.686 --> 20:55.558
♪ Tonight♪

20:55.689 --> 20:59.301
♪ They'll come true♪

20:59.432 --> 21:04.567
♪ In the end.♪

21:05.525 --> 21:07.570
[cheering, applause]

21:13.489 --> 21:15.143
It worked.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.928
Oh, I am proud of you, Agnes.

21:18.059 --> 21:20.061
Thank you for the flood
of endorphins, by the way.

21:20.191 --> 21:23.847
Those nasty little stress
hormones were getting in my way.

21:23.978 --> 21:25.501
What's happening?

21:25.632 --> 21:27.808
This was my plan all along.

21:27.938 --> 21:31.333
Finally, the endorphins
I needed.

21:32.334 --> 21:34.554
I think I'll steer
this ship for a while.

21:35.598 --> 21:37.905
No, wait. I-I'm in control.

21:38.035 --> 21:40.081
Not anymore.

21:49.525 --> 21:51.397
PICARD:
You seem upset.

21:51.527 --> 21:54.704
I-I'm sorry.
I don't want to be rude, but...

21:54.835 --> 21:57.185
I'd like to be alone, okay?

21:57.316 --> 22:00.014
In my experience,
when I'm distraught,

22:00.144 --> 22:02.930
I find talking about
something else often helps.

22:03.060 --> 22:05.976
Any suggestions then?

22:07.282 --> 22:09.153
Look up.

22:10.198 --> 22:13.114
Can you tell me about that ship?

22:17.336 --> 22:19.686
OV-165 shuttle.

22:22.384 --> 22:24.212
I call her "Spike"

22:24.343 --> 22:26.997
because she's got these
kick-ass aerospike engines

22:27.128 --> 22:29.652
that use less fuel.

22:32.438 --> 22:34.048
I don't...

22:34.178 --> 22:36.311
mean any offense, but...

22:36.442 --> 22:39.358
you seem a little up in years
to be a security guard.

22:39.488 --> 22:41.360
True.

22:41.490 --> 22:43.274
But...

22:43.405 --> 22:46.365
I am the wisest of them all.

22:46.495 --> 22:49.063
I bet you're thinking
they let anyone

22:49.193 --> 22:52.153
be an astronaut these days.

22:52.283 --> 22:54.503
Sometimes those

22:54.634 --> 22:56.505
who shine the brightest

22:56.636 --> 22:59.378
feel the sting
of fear and melancholy

22:59.508 --> 23:01.510
in ways that others

23:01.641 --> 23:04.339
can never understand.

23:04.470 --> 23:07.298
You're talking like you know me.

23:07.429 --> 23:10.040
You're Renée Picard, astronaut

23:10.171 --> 23:12.521
of the Europa Mission.

23:12.652 --> 23:15.045
You must be capable
of such great things

23:15.176 --> 23:17.396
to have come this far.

23:23.663 --> 23:26.709
You remind me
a bit of my mother.

23:27.884 --> 23:29.886
She, too,

23:30.017 --> 23:32.411
loved the stars.

23:32.541 --> 23:35.370
And she, too...

23:35.501 --> 23:38.373
struggled.

23:41.811 --> 23:44.205
Sometimes fear is
a friendly reminder

23:44.335 --> 23:45.772
you're not ready for something.

23:45.902 --> 23:47.382
No.

23:47.513 --> 23:50.037
Fear is fear.

23:50.167 --> 23:51.995
It doesn't speak in riddles.

23:52.126 --> 23:54.215
Fear means...

23:54.345 --> 23:55.999
you're smart.

23:56.130 --> 23:59.002
You understand the risks.

23:59.133 --> 24:01.265
So what are you afraid of?

24:01.396 --> 24:03.485
I don't know
where I would begin.

24:03.616 --> 24:05.966
[chuckles]

24:06.096 --> 24:08.447
And you found a way
to live with it?

24:09.535 --> 24:11.885
I've found that even in

24:12.015 --> 24:14.365
the darkest circumstances,

24:14.496 --> 24:16.542
there is a light.

24:16.672 --> 24:20.110
Sometimes only a glimmer.

24:20.241 --> 24:22.548
Trust that light.

24:22.678 --> 24:24.985
Find a way back.

24:25.115 --> 24:27.466
No matter what it takes.

24:30.381 --> 24:32.383
Your mother

24:32.514 --> 24:35.125
was very lucky to have you.

24:35.256 --> 24:38.041
WOMAN:
Jean-Luc?

24:38.172 --> 24:39.739
Come and find me.

24:39.869 --> 24:41.784
BOY:
Maman. Maman!

24:44.831 --> 24:46.180
Well.

24:46.310 --> 24:48.704
Oh, I almost forgot.

24:48.835 --> 24:51.098
I was sent to collect you.

24:51.228 --> 24:53.361
Dr. Jemison is gonna
make a toast.

24:53.492 --> 24:56.277
They want all
the astronauts on the stage.

24:59.454 --> 25:01.761
Will you be joining them?

25:03.719 --> 25:05.025
I will.

25:22.346 --> 25:24.392
-[crowd clamoring]
-[cameras clicking]

25:39.059 --> 25:41.409
Q:
I want you to remove
an obstacle.

25:41.540 --> 25:43.977
Renée Picard.

25:48.242 --> 25:50.418
RENEÉE:
Going around the outside
will get us there the quickest.

25:52.638 --> 25:55.858
I'm afraid
this is as far as I go.

25:58.557 --> 26:01.429
Thanks again for the pep talk.

26:01.560 --> 26:04.911
I don't suppose you want
to catch a ride to Europa?

26:05.041 --> 26:07.391
I feel like you could
hang in the cockpit,

26:07.522 --> 26:09.393
keep everyone calm.

26:09.524 --> 26:12.396
Ooh, I'm very tempted.

26:12.527 --> 26:15.356
But, uh, perhaps another time?

26:15.486 --> 26:18.315
Why do I feel like I know you?

26:19.403 --> 26:21.231
[tires screech]

26:21.362 --> 26:23.059
[Renée screams]

26:23.190 --> 26:25.409
[Picard exclaims]

26:26.976 --> 26:28.587
[tires screech]

26:28.717 --> 26:30.545
[crowd murmuring, clamoring]

26:30.676 --> 26:31.807
RIOS:
Admiral!

26:38.118 --> 26:40.424
-He's got a pulse.
-Okay, we have to get him
to a hospital.

26:40.555 --> 26:42.296
-They'll want ID.
-What about your ship?

26:42.426 --> 26:44.472
A biobed is not a doctor.

26:46.213 --> 26:48.258
I know someone.

26:50.870 --> 26:52.915
Admiral, stay with us.

27:02.316 --> 27:05.014
[monitor beeping rhythmically]

27:05.145 --> 27:07.887
Does he have any conditions?

27:09.236 --> 27:11.978
He's... had some transplants.

27:12.108 --> 27:15.285
-Some? How many?
-All of them.

27:15.416 --> 27:17.592
[rapid beeping]

27:20.116 --> 27:22.292
He's got an unstable arrhythmia.

27:22.423 --> 27:24.207
-His heart's all over the place.
-RIOS: What does that mean?

27:24.338 --> 27:27.167
It means he's in the middle
of a major cardiac event.

27:29.473 --> 27:31.214
[electricity humming]

27:31.345 --> 27:32.868
Clear!

27:34.391 --> 27:35.479
[monitor beeping rhythmically]

27:35.610 --> 27:37.699
Is he okay?

27:40.136 --> 27:42.225
TERESA:
He's back in normal sinus.

27:42.356 --> 27:45.185
-Blood pressure is stabilizing.
-RAFFI: Okay.

27:45.315 --> 27:46.752
Teresa--

27:46.882 --> 27:49.493
Everybody out!

28:08.599 --> 28:10.514
-[door chimes]
-[steam hissing]

28:13.387 --> 28:15.476
My God! What happened to you?

28:15.606 --> 28:17.783
I'm fine.

28:20.655 --> 28:22.701
[exhales]

28:24.093 --> 28:25.616
[sighs]

28:25.747 --> 28:28.315
All my life...

28:28.445 --> 28:30.796
all my life I've invented.

28:30.926 --> 28:32.623
Machines.

28:32.754 --> 28:34.625
Medicine.

28:34.756 --> 28:36.802
I knew I could bend the rules.

28:36.932 --> 28:38.847
Take the risks.

28:38.978 --> 28:41.502
Were you driving?

28:41.632 --> 28:43.330
Do I need to call someone?

28:43.460 --> 28:45.854
I poured my heart into you.

28:46.899 --> 28:48.944
I let myself believe

28:49.075 --> 28:50.641
you were the one.

28:50.772 --> 28:53.209
You'd make it.

28:53.340 --> 28:55.211
And now...

28:55.342 --> 28:57.387
after everything I did...

28:57.518 --> 28:58.954
[sighs]

28:59.085 --> 29:01.870
...realized
what I'm capable of doing...

29:03.611 --> 29:06.135
[stammers]
...I still failed.

29:08.398 --> 29:10.749
I'm still going to lose you.

29:12.228 --> 29:15.492
-My life's work.
-You're scaring me.

29:15.623 --> 29:18.017
I'm so sorry.

29:18.147 --> 29:19.758
I didn't stop her!

29:21.107 --> 29:23.022
I may have stopped him,
collateral.

29:23.152 --> 29:24.458
-But not her.
-Dad!

29:24.588 --> 29:26.590
It's me. Why are you
talking like this?

29:26.721 --> 29:27.896
Why?

29:28.027 --> 29:29.985
The why matters.

29:30.116 --> 29:32.292
The why of things matters.

29:33.380 --> 29:35.382
And you...

29:35.512 --> 29:38.254
you are my why.

29:38.385 --> 29:40.822
Saving you.

29:40.953 --> 29:42.998
My life's work.

29:47.786 --> 29:49.309
Dad?

29:50.614 --> 29:52.834
Dad, just be honest with me.

29:54.967 --> 29:57.012
[door opens]

29:58.100 --> 30:00.146
[door closes]

30:04.890 --> 30:06.587
So...

30:06.717 --> 30:08.981
Jurati can sing.

30:09.111 --> 30:10.983
Any word from her?

30:11.113 --> 30:12.375
RIOS:
Nope.

30:12.506 --> 30:13.507
TALLINN:
We did succeed in getting Renée

30:13.637 --> 30:14.813
into quarantine.

30:14.943 --> 30:16.292
[latch clicks]

30:16.423 --> 30:17.859
He's stable.

30:17.990 --> 30:19.295
But non-responsive.

30:19.426 --> 30:20.819
I'll be back in an hour.

30:20.949 --> 30:22.690
I have a son
who's about to wake up

30:22.821 --> 30:25.519
and wonder where I am
for the second time this week.

30:25.649 --> 30:26.825
How long will he be out?

30:26.955 --> 30:28.652
Honestly...

30:28.783 --> 30:31.438
I don't know.
Everything's working.

30:31.568 --> 30:33.962
-I'm not sure
why he's not waking up.
-Well, not good enough.

30:34.093 --> 30:36.356
-She's doing the best she can.
-I don't need your help.

30:36.486 --> 30:37.879
Okay, can we see him now?

30:38.010 --> 30:40.708
-Sure.
-RAFFI: Thank you.

30:46.627 --> 30:48.716
-I know this is nuts.
-Nah.

30:48.847 --> 30:51.240
It was super fun
coming to my raided clinic

30:51.371 --> 30:53.068
in the middle of the night
and sticking my hands

30:53.199 --> 30:54.635
in your boss' chest.

30:54.765 --> 30:56.942
You came.

30:59.466 --> 31:02.295
I've used a defibrillator
way more times

31:02.425 --> 31:04.558
than I can count.

31:04.688 --> 31:06.342
Maybe your kid
was messing with it.

31:06.473 --> 31:07.778
Cranked it.
[chuckles]

31:07.909 --> 31:09.998
Deep respect for a grown man

31:10.129 --> 31:12.174
who will scapegoat
an innocent child.

31:17.353 --> 31:19.660
Who are you?

31:20.835 --> 31:22.489
[sighs]
I know what it looks like.

31:22.619 --> 31:24.839
Or-or not, but...

31:24.970 --> 31:26.623
trust me.

31:26.754 --> 31:28.799
We're the good guys.

31:30.845 --> 31:32.891
Good guys never say that.

31:38.331 --> 31:40.376
-[beeping]
-[door opens]

31:43.902 --> 31:45.904
[blipping and beeping]

32:17.326 --> 32:19.763
♪

32:26.205 --> 32:28.772
I think this is good.

32:28.903 --> 32:30.949
I think we're good here.

32:31.079 --> 32:33.734
-Hello, little girl.
-Hi.

32:33.864 --> 32:36.389
-SOONG: Where do you live?
-Why don't I remember this?

32:36.519 --> 32:39.218
-In a cave.
-In a cave? I don't--

32:39.348 --> 32:40.959
Before I give you
a piece of cake,

32:41.089 --> 32:43.744
I need you to close your eyes
and make a wish.

32:46.616 --> 32:48.836
Why have I never seen
this photo?

32:51.795 --> 32:53.493
Or any of these?

32:56.975 --> 32:59.325
SOONG:
July 11.

32:59.455 --> 33:02.067
Today was a good day.

33:02.197 --> 33:04.852
Life signs are looking up.

33:04.983 --> 33:07.028
I estimate Persephone has a 97%

33:07.159 --> 33:09.030
chance of survival.

33:10.249 --> 33:12.642
August 12, Friday.

33:12.773 --> 33:15.515
Persephone died
from complications.

33:15.645 --> 33:17.517
One month old.

33:19.301 --> 33:21.825
KORE:
Who the hell is Persephone?

33:25.916 --> 33:27.440
January 23.

33:27.570 --> 33:29.833
Despoina, age three.

33:29.964 --> 33:33.141
Persephatta's liver failure
caused her brain to swell.

33:33.272 --> 33:34.708
Artemis is currently
in the midst of...

33:34.838 --> 33:38.103
[overlapping conversations]

33:46.198 --> 33:47.721
Today...

33:47.851 --> 33:49.897
was a hard one.

33:52.030 --> 33:54.815
Frustration got
the better of me.

33:55.772 --> 33:57.992
I know now...

33:58.123 --> 34:01.213
this one will be the last.

34:01.343 --> 34:03.867
[inhales deeply]
And there's a...

34:05.695 --> 34:09.047
There's a sense of release
in that.

34:09.177 --> 34:12.963
I will do anything
and everything

34:13.094 --> 34:15.792
to make sure she survives.

34:17.055 --> 34:19.448
Kore.

34:24.366 --> 34:26.934
KORE:
What am I?

34:28.196 --> 34:30.764
Dad, what did you do?

34:36.726 --> 34:40.426
TALLINN:
His amygdala is responding
as if he's in imminent danger.

34:40.556 --> 34:43.342
All of his synapses are firing.

34:44.343 --> 34:46.475
SEVEN OF NINE:
That doesn't seem right.

34:46.606 --> 34:49.087
Brain activity should be minimal
in a coma.

34:49.217 --> 34:51.045
Exactly.

34:51.176 --> 34:53.656
The doctor doesn't know
why he's still out.

34:55.615 --> 34:57.225
What if this is mental?

34:57.356 --> 35:00.359
All of his vital signs
appear normal.

35:00.489 --> 35:02.665
There's no brain swelling.

35:02.796 --> 35:04.363
No brain bleed.

35:04.493 --> 35:07.192
Jean-Luc, look up at the stars.

35:09.237 --> 35:11.631
You have to get me out.
Jean-Luc, please!

35:11.761 --> 35:14.024
[screaming]

35:16.201 --> 35:19.029
Uh... what's happening?

35:19.160 --> 35:21.423
He's stuck in there.

35:21.554 --> 35:24.426
And the longer he is,

35:24.557 --> 35:27.603
the harder it'll be
to ever get him out.

35:31.129 --> 35:33.392
I could go in.

35:33.522 --> 35:35.307
Sorry, what now?

35:35.437 --> 35:37.961
In... side him?

35:38.092 --> 35:40.138
Maybe I can pull him out.

35:40.268 --> 35:42.314
Using
my neuro-optic interceptor.

35:43.315 --> 35:45.621
The same synaptic pathways
I hijack

35:45.752 --> 35:48.233
to look outwards,
could be travelled in.

35:48.363 --> 35:50.539
To the subconscious.

35:50.670 --> 35:53.847
A kind of jury-rigged mind meld.

35:53.977 --> 35:56.545
Once I gain access to his mind,

35:56.676 --> 35:58.199
I can hack into whatever memory

35:58.330 --> 36:00.201
or thought he's fixated on.

36:00.332 --> 36:02.856
In theory, interact with it.

36:02.986 --> 36:04.945
Take his lead,
get him show me how

36:05.075 --> 36:06.164
-to help him out.
-No

36:06.294 --> 36:07.991
No!

36:08.122 --> 36:09.341
[stammers]

36:09.471 --> 36:12.431
His brain is comatose
for a reason.

36:12.561 --> 36:15.042
-It's protective.
-A lot of what we do
is protective.

36:15.173 --> 36:17.479
It doesn't mean
it's good for us.

36:17.610 --> 36:18.959
Guys? No.

36:19.089 --> 36:21.048
-Am I right?
-TALLINN: As long

36:21.179 --> 36:23.659
as Renée is being
targeted by a god,

36:23.790 --> 36:26.488
or whatever this Q is,
no safe house on earth

